      "text": [
        " «لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ» وَ سَأَلَهُ عَنِ اَلرَّجُلِ يَطَّلِي قَبْلَ أَنْ يَأْتِيَ مَكَّةَ بِسَبْعِ لَيَالٍ أَوْ ثَمَانِ لَيَالٍ قَالَ «لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2535 - Mu‘awiyah ibn Ammar asked about a man who removes hair (yattili) six nights before reaching the miqat.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it.\"\nHe also asked about a man who removes hair seven or eight nights before reaching Makkah.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
